27/06/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The government is determined to press ahead with its planned structural reforms, particularly in social security, despite the threat of ongoing labour unrest.
On Saturday (25 June) Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis, Economy and Finance Minister Giorgos Alogoskoufis and Development Minister Dimitris Sioufas held a meeting and reiterated their commitment to the reform programme.
Meanwhile, employees in the banking sector plan a fourth week of protests against a government bill to restructure bank employees' pensions.
Local media are reporting that cash machines in Greece are running out of money.
(Kathimerini - 27/06/05;
ANA - 26/06/05)
